               <para.body>Given vectors <math>
                     <latex>\Vect{x}</latex>
                  </math> and <math>
                     <latex>\Vect{y}</latex>
                  </math>, the triangle inequality <math>
                     <latex>|\Vect{x} + \Vect{y}| \leq |\Vect{x}| + |\Vect{y}|</latex>
                  </math> deserves its name: It asserts that in a triangle any one edge is at most as long as the sum of the other two.</para.body>
